{
  "texts": [
    "This data-driven foundation enables them to tackle semantic challenges where traditional methods often fall short.",
    "They can generate complex inputs with domain-specific semantics [59,67], construct effective test prefixes [108,170], and produce reasonable mock implementations for external dependencies [54,108,116].The introduction of LLMs has led to a rapid increase in research on unit test generation, but it has also brought new challenges and a diversity of methods.",
    "While existing surveys have broadly reviewed the application of LLMs in software engineering [40,166] or offered initial classifications of the task [165], they have largely focused on cataloging existing work.",
    "This survey argues that the development of LLM-based test generation involves adapting classic software engineering (SE) principles and enhancing LLMs, treating them as stochastic generators that require systematic constraints.Through a systematic analysis of 115 publications, this paper presents this technical taxonomy.",
    "Our analysis reveals that the research community has rapidly integrated classic SE techniques with LLMs."
  ]
}